The paper proposes a new strategy that combines machine learning with numerical models to discover hidden laws governing dynamical systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of automatic differentiation libraries, which suggests that it may also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and/or the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) categories. Finally, the paper involves an application to upper ocean dynamics, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) category.
